    "iiiiiiiiimiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiHimiiiimiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiimiium The Toiler E ONE YEAR I BUNDLE RATES I SIS MONTHS 200 350 Per Hundred 8100 E Address all mail and make all checks payable to THE TOILER 3207 Clark Ave Cleveland Ohio Kntered as Second Class Matter under the name ef The E Ohio Socialist February 21 1917 at the Post Office at E Cleveland O Under the Act of March 3 1879 E EDITOR Elmer T Allison E Published weekly by the Toiler PubUshing Association Telephone Harvard 3639 EDITORIAL CLEVELAND 0 FRIDAY JULY 30th 1920 niiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiMiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiiim Uncle Sam Scab Herder If there is any one who had any illusions of the outcome of the results of the deliberations of the Railway Labor Board they must be sufficiently dissillusioned now That the decision simply throws a sop to the railway workers in the hope of keeping down their clamoring for a living wage is apparent The award of 600000000 sounds big but when it is measured by the individual share of the J workers it dwindles into insignificance With a calculation which placed the award barely above the deadline at which the workers would refuse it the board made its award with a surety that it would be"
